      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "> Ideally, this should be fixed before we enable Cirrus Ci for bitcoin/bitcoin\r\n\r\nYes, nothing specific to Cirrus: but in general, the rationale to not add more CIs is that currently the CI situation is already somewhat like a slot machine, with tests failing more often randomly than due to actual problems, we don't want to make it worse.\r\n(Add to that that every CI has its own way to restart the build, and a different way of access control who gets to reset the build)",
